"graphics32/graphics32\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END-->. <code>[Delphi]</code> <code>[FPC]</code> Designed for fast 32-bit graphics handling on Delphi, Kylix and Lazarus. Optimized for 32-bit pixel formats, it provides fast operations with pixels and graphic primitives, and in most cases Graphics32 outperforms the standard TCanvas classes. It is almost a hundred times faster in per-pixel access and about 2-5 times faster in drawing lines.</li>","updatedAt":"2019-02-04T15:01:32.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"Fr0sT-Brutal/awesome-pascal","categoryHTML":"<h2>Graphic</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://www.kluug.net/delphitwain.php\">Delphi Twain</a>. <code>[Delphi]</code> <code>[FPC]</code> The library allows you to easily access scanning functions from Delphi and Lazarus.</li>","updatedAt":"2019-02-04T15:01:32.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"Fr0sT-Brutal/awesome-pascal","categoryHTML":"<h2>Game dev</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/BeRo1985/kraft\">Kraft Physics Engine</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/BeRo1985/kraft\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">72</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":72,\"repo\":\"BeRo1985/kraft\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END-->. <code>[Delphi]</code> <code>[FPC]</code> Open source Object Pascal physics engine library that can be used in 3D games. Compatible with: Delphi 7-XE7 (but not with the Android and iOS targets), FreePascal >= 2.6.2 (with almost all FPC-supported targets including Android and iOS)</li>","updatedAt":"2019-02-04T15:01:32.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"Fr0sT-Brutal/awesome-pascal","categoryHTML":"<h2>Network</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/IndySockets/Indy\">Indy</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/IndySockets/Indy\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">230</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":230,\"repo\":\"IndySockets/Indy\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END-->. <code>[Delphi]</code> <code>[FPC]</code> Network components for Delphi, C++Builder, Delphi.NET, and FreePascal</li>","updatedAt":"2019-02-04T15:01:32.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"Fr0sT-Brutal/awesome-pascal","categoryHTML":"<h2>Database</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://sourceforge.net/projects/zeoslib\">ZeosLib</a>. <code>[Delphi]</code> <code>[FPC]</code> Set of database components for MySQL, PostgreSQL, Interbase, Firebird, MS SQL, Sybase, Oracle and SQLite.</li>","updatedAt":"2019-02-04T15:01:32.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"Fr0sT-Brutal/awesome-pascal","categoryHTML":"<h2>Scripting</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/remobjects/pascalscript\">Pascal Script</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/remobjects/pascalscript\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">316</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":316,\"repo\":\"remobjects/pascalscript\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END-->. <code>[Delphi]</code> <code>[FPC]</code> Free scripting engine that allows you to use most of the Object Pascal language within your Delphi or Free Pascal projects at runtime. Written completely in Delphi, it is composed of a set of units that can be compiled into your executable, eliminating the need to distribute any external files. Pascal Script started out as a need for a good working script, when there were none available at the time.</li>","updatedAt":"2019-02-04T15:01:32.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"Fr0sT-Brutal/awesome-pascal","categoryHTML":"<h2>Template</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/synopse/dmustache\">SynMustache</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/synopse/dmustache\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">110</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":110,\"repo\":\"synopse/dmustache\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END-->. <code>[Delphi]</code> <code>[FPC]</code> Delphi implementation of the Mustache template language, supporting Delphi 6 up to Delphi 10 Seattle (and FPC/Lazarus compilation).</li>","updatedAt":"2019-02-04T15:01:32.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"Fr0sT-Brutal/awesome-pascal","categoryHTML":"<h2>Logging</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/exilon/QuickLogger\">QuickLogger</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/exilon/QuickLogger\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">144</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":144,\"repo\":\"exilon/QuickLogger\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END-->. <code>[Delphi]</code> <code>[FPC]</code> Delphi/freepascal/.NET (Windows/Linux) library for logging on files, console, memory, email, rest, telegram, slack, eventlog, redis, ide debug messages and throw events..</li>","updatedAt":"2019-02-04T15:01:32.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"Fr0sT-Brutal/awesome-pascal","categoryHTML":"<h2>Other non-visual</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/BeRo1985/flre\">FLRE</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/BeRo1985/flre\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">66</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":66,\"repo\":\"BeRo1985/flre\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END-->. <code>[Delphi]</code> <code>[FPC]</code> FLRE ( F ast L ight R egular E xpressions) is a fast, safe and efficient regular expression library, which is implemented in Object Pascal (Delphi and Free Pascal) but which is even usable from other languages like C/C++ and so on.</li>","updatedAt":"2019-02-04T15:01:32.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"Fr0sT-Brutal/awesome-pascal","categoryHTML":"<h2>OS</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/RRUZ/tsmbios\">TSMBIOS</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/RRUZ/tsmbios\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">142</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":142,\"repo\":\"RRUZ/tsmbios\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END-->. <code>[Delphi]</code> <code>[FPC]</code> Allows access the System Management BIOS (SMBIOS) using the Object Pascal language (Delphi or Free Pascal). The SMBIOS (System Management BIOS) is a standard developed by the DMTF. The information stored in the SMBIOS includes devices manufacturer, model name, serial number, BIOS version, asset tag, processors, ports and device memory installed.</li>","updatedAt":"2019-02-04T15:01:32.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"avelino/awesome-go","categoryHTML":"<h2>Websites</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://hashnode.com/n/go\">Go Community on Hashnode</a> - Community of Gophers on Hashnode.</li>","updatedAt":"2019-02-04T11:43:34.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"avelino/awesome-go","categoryHTML":"<h2>Data Structures</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/edwingeng/deque\">deque</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/edwingeng/deque\" style=\"text-decora